sentences: George Herman Buck Jr. (December 22, 1928 – December 11, 2013) was an American entrepreneur who devoted much of his life to recording jazz by producing albums and acquiring the rights to those produced by companies established by others.
The GHB Jazz Foundation houses the record business and is located on the second floor of the same building in the French Quarter.
As of 4-2-2020, Buck's weekly program Jazzology continues to air on WAVO 1150-AM in Rock Hill, SC on Sundays from 4-5PM.
He produced nearly 700 broadcasts during his years in New Orleans.
In recent years, most of the programs were transferred to compact discs.
